# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Cargo lock — committed for binary crates, ignored for libraries.
# ampaper is a binary so we keep Cargo.lock under version control;
# this line stays here as a placeholder so a future split into a
# lib crate can flip the policy without churn.

# IDE
/.vscode
/.idea
*.iml

# OS
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# Local scratch
/scratch
/tmp
*.log

# .vscode tasks.json redirect target — captures GUI stdout/stderr
# from Ctrl+Shift+B. Local dev artefact, not ground truth.
/swaplog.txt

# Reference vendoring (the original paperbak-1.10.src and the
# mrpods checkout sit under /reference/ when present, but we do
# NOT ship them in our repo — they are read-only ground truth
# for cross-checking and have their own licenses + upstreams.
/reference
